Armed policemen in Abuja have opened fire on human rights activist, Omoyele Sowore during a protest to demand an end to insecurity in the country. Sowore was shot in the right side of the stomach towards the hip by gun-wielding policemen drafted to the Unity Fountain.  The police who had already been stationed at the fountain before the arrival of the activist and other protesters opened fire on the unarmed protesters.  Just been shit by a police officer, ACP Atine at the Unity Fountain in Abuja. #RevolutionNow Let the struggle continue even if they take my life! #BuhariMustGo pic.twitter.com/c9ui2UutXO  Many people also sustained varying degrees of injury during the incident. He has been rushed to an undisclosed hospital. 